Training: Policy Gradient Algorithm via REINFORCE
In this section, we leverage policy gradient methods to train the stochastic cut-selection policy πθ via
the REINFORCE algorithm [Williams, 1992] (see Algorithm 1). One training episode corresponds
to one complete BD trajectory. During each episode, at each iteration t, the algorithm records the
current state st, the selected cuts At, their log-probabilities log Pθ(At|st), and the stepwise reward rt.
